Conclusion:
I choose Powerage because, despite being a studio album, its raw, guitar‑driven character and mastering that preserves warmth and dynamics better fit my preference for performance energy, organic tonal colors, and mixes that favor feel and momentum. I reject Vault because it is a tightly sequenced, highly polished greatest‑hits compilation engineered for radio/stadium impact — the very over‑produced, artificially sequenced, and compressed characteristics I stated I dislike.

